Southern Kaduna progressive Forum has expressed satisfaction with the representation of Senator Danjuma La’ah representing Kaduna Southern zone in the Senate. The forum in a statement signed by Amos Christopher, said Senator La’ah has touched many lives in many ways, invested most of his resources in the zone, and that he is a philanthropist and a businessman who has love and passion for his people even before  joining politics. “The Senator has been the only senator that broke the jinx of one term syndrome in the history of southern Kaduna since the return of democracy in 1999. Besides, the distinguished senator is a philanthropist and a businessman who has love and passion for his people. Even before joining politics he has invested most of his resources in the zone. “Regarding some of his performances, the senator has moved a bill for the conversion of the Federal school of statistics Manchok to federal University of Technology which has passed third reading awaiting approval from presidency to commence operation. “On the issue of establishing Federal Medical Centre Kafanchan, it is on record that senator La’ah is up and doing so that the medical centre come to reality in order to improve the health standard of the people. A team of health experts were sent from the Federal Ministry of Health to Kafanchan for an evaluation already. “An allegation in the said write up was that of siting projects in the Senators’ area alone and neglecting other areas. But contrary, senator La’ah donated plots of land, built and furnished it to standard in Kagoro and then donated it to national open university (NOUN) as a study center to promote education in the zone,” the rejoinder partly read. It added also that Senator La’ah is not bias in terms of appointments because one Suleiman Isa who is a Legislative Aide to Senator La’ah, is a Muslim and Fulani by tribe. Another is the likes of Baba Douglas from Sanga local government area and Nimzom by tribe, among others.